@startuml Recommendation Engine Activity Diagram
title Recommendation Engine - Activity Diagram

|System|
start

:Start nightly cron job;

== Data Collection & Processing ==

fork
  :Collect user explicit preferences
  (location, budget, property type, amenities);
fork again
  :Aggregate implicit behavior signals
  (views, favorites, search queries, time spent);
fork again
  :Extract listing features
  (description, amenities, location, price);
end fork

:Build feature vector pipeline;
:Generate user preference vectors;
:Create listing embeddings using TF-IDF;

== ML Model Execution ==

:Apply k-means clustering
to group similar properties;

if (User has sufficient history?) then (yes)
  :Calculate hybrid score:
  60% explicit preferences
  + 40% implicit signals;
  :Rank listings by relevance score;
  :Select top recommendations;
else (no - Cold Start)
  :Fetch popular/trending listings
  in user's region;
  :Apply basic filters
  (budget, property type);
  :Select fallback recommendations;
endif

:Store recommendations in database;
:Cache results in Redis (24h TTL);
:Log refresh timestamp;

== User Interaction ==

|Tenant|
:Log in to platform;
:View dashboard;
:See "Recommended for You" section;

repeat
  :Browse recommended listings;
  
  if (Action taken?) then (view listing)
    |System|
    :Track view event;
    :Update behavior signals;
    :Increment engagement metrics;
    |Tenant|
  elseif (Action taken?) then (add to favorites)
    |System|
    :Track favorite event;
    :Increase preference weight for similar listings;
    :Update CTR metrics;
    |Tenant|
  elseif (Action taken?) then (submit inquiry)
    |System|
    :Track inquiry event;
    :Record conversion metric;
    :Boost relevance score for similar properties;
    |Tenant|
  elseif (Action taken?) then (click "Not Interested")
    |System|
    :Record negative feedback;
    :Hide listing from future recommendations;
    :Update exclusion list;
    :Refine algorithm parameters;
    |Tenant|
    :Remove listing from view with animation;
  elseif (Action taken?) then (click "Why this?")
    |System|
    :Fetch explanation via /explain/:id;
    :Analyze matching factors;
    :Generate human-readable reasons;
    |Tenant|
    :View tooltip with matching criteria
    (e.g., "Matches your budget and preferred location");
  endif
  
backward :Continue browsing;
repeat while (More recommendations to view?) is (yes)
->no;

== Weekly Email Digest ==

|System|
:Check day and time;
if (Monday 9 AM?) then (yes)
  fork
    :Query top 5 recommendations per user;
    :Include new arrivals matching preferences;
    :Generate personalized email template;
    :Send weekly digest email;
  end fork
  
  |Tenant|
  :Receive email notification;
  if (Click email link?) then (yes)
    :Redirect to platform;
    :View recommended listings;
  endif
endif

== Admin Monitoring ==

|Admin|
fork
  :Open recommendation analytics dashboard;
  :View performance metrics:
  - Click-through rate (CTR)
  - Saves/favorites count
  - Inquiries from recommendations;
  :Analyze weekly trend charts;
  :Review breakdown by property type and location;
  
  if (Quality issues detected?) then (yes)
    :Click pause/resume toggle;
    |System|
    :Disable recommendation engine globally;
    :Update status to 'Paused';
    :Log admin action;
    :Display pause status indicator;
    |Admin|
    :Investigate and fix issues;
    :Resume engine when ready;
    |System|
    :Re-enable recommendations;
    :Update status to 'Active';
  endif
end fork

== Continuous Improvement ==

|System|
repeat
  :Collect feedback loop data;
  :Analyze hidden/flagged listings;
  :Calculate recommendation accuracy;
  :Fine-tune scoring weights;
  :Update ML model parameters;
  :Optimize query performance;
backward :Wait for next refresh cycle;
repeat while (Next nightly cron job?) is (not yet)
->triggered;

:Repeat recommendation generation;

stop

@enduml
